<opener><address><addrLine>Council Chamber,
Fermoy,</address> 
<dateline><date>26th May 1916</date></dateline></addrLine>
<addrLine>To.
<address>His Excellency Baron Wimborne</addrLine>
<addrLine>Lord Lieutenant of Ireland. Dublin Castle.</addrLine></address>

<salute>May it please Your Excellency:</salute></opener>
<p>I am directed by the Fermoy Urban
<lb/>Council to transmit to you the undermentioned Resolution in
<lb/>reference to the Malicious Injury Claim lodged by Mrs Rowe for
<lb/>£2500 compensation for the death of her husband the late Head Const
<lb/>Rowe, which occurred on the 2nd inst.</p>
<salute>I remain,
<lb/>Your Excellency's,
<lb/>Most Obedient Servant</salute>
<signed>Wm Sheehan</signed>
<lb/>Town Clerk.

<lb/>Copy Resolution
<p>"That solely with a view to the continuance of the
<lb/>"good, peaceable, and law abiding character of this District, and to
<lb/>"obviate any cause of friction or ill feeling, We most earnestly urge
<lb/>"on the Authorities to provide out of some fund at their disposal such
<lb/>"compensation to the Family of the late Head Constable Rowe R.I.C,
<lb/>"Fermoy, as they may justly be considered <sic>entutled</sic> to for his loss which
<lb/>"we all regret, and that the pending application of his Widow for
<lb/>"compensation to be levied off the Ratepayers should be withdrawn.
<lb/>"We do not desire to express any opinion as to the merits or otherwise
<lb/>"of the application, but we consider that the levying of such a Decree
<lb/>"for compensation off the Ratepayers would inevitably provoke a
<lb/>"disturbance of the peace of the District and lead to a repetition of
<lb/>"the unfortunate occurrences with which this Barony of Condons and
<lb/>Clongibbons was visited in the Eighties".</p>

<note>I ack
<lb/> II <gap/>
<lb/> Please say what pension
<lb/> may be paid to Mrs Rowe under
<lb/> the R.I.C. Acts. 29-5-16</note>
        
    

    
                </body>
            </text>

        
            
        

         

